info.senderName: NWS Key West (Key West - The Florida Keys)
info.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued December 18 at 10:47AM EST until December 18 at 5:00PM EST by NWS Key West
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 PM EST THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...Current water levels continue falling, but for now, remain at Advisory levels for the Bayside communities of Key Largo. * WHERE...Upper Florida Keys. * WHEN...Until 5 PM EST this afternoon. * IMPACTS...Saltwater flooding of low elevation streets and lots is expected. Some storm drains will overflow, and some seawalls and docks will be overtopped. Boaters can expect less clearance under fixed bridges. Motorists should remember that persistent puddles around the times of high tide are almost certain to contain a mix of saltwater.
info.instruction: If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property.
